unkempt
proposition 

My bangs are getting a bit long and starting to bother me—definitely time for a trim.

When my bangs get too long, I feel like I look tired or unkempt, which can affect how others see me. If I look sharp and refreshed, people are more likely to come up and start a conversation. But if I don't, they tend to stay away.

Honestly, I think hairstyle plays an even bigger role in overall appearance than things like clothes. So I really need to start paying more attention to how my hair looks.




A: Ugh, my bangs are getting so long—they’re really starting to annoy me.
B: Time for a trim?
A: Yeah, definitely. When my bangs get like this, I just feel like I look tired or kinda messy.
B: I get that. It really does change your whole vibe.
A: Exactly! If I look more fresh and put-together, people actually come up and talk to me. But if I look all out of it, they just don’t.
B: Makes sense. Hair’s a huge part of your overall look.
A: Right? Honestly, I think it matters even more than clothes. I really need to start paying more attention to it.


